The '''Corellian Sanctuary''' was a small, domed building on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], built after the [[Liberation of Coruscant (Galactic Civil War)|Seizure of Coruscant]]. It was created by exiled [[Corellian/Legends|Corellians]] as a resting place for their [[Death/Legends|dead]], as hostility between the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and the [[Diktat]] [[Daclif Gallamby]] meant the dead could not be returned to their native planet. The bodies of the deceased were cremated, and industrial-grade gravity generators used to compress the carbon residue into raw [[synthetic diamond]]s. The diamonds were brought to the Sanctuary and embedded into the black walls and ceiling to create a glittering series of constellations, as seen from Corellia.

By [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], following an [[Coruscant terrorist attacks and riots|attack on Coruscant]] by Corellian dissidents during the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], the sanctuary was vandalized by citizens of Coruscant who stole many of the compressed diamonds, causing more Corellians to rebel against the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]]. Many of the local Corellians attempted to clean up the Sanctuary, though they were never able to recover all of the diamonds. It was here that [[Ben Skywalker]] met [[Barit Saiy]].

